<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Composio Integration Readiness Report — 100 SaaS Applications</title>
<script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/Chart.js/4.4.1/chart.umd.min.js"></script>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Grotesk:wght@500;600;700&family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<script>
  tailwind.config = {
    theme: {
      extend: {
        colors: {
          bg: '#0A0E17', surface: '#111827', surface2: '#161F33', line: '#232D42',
          ink: '#E7ECF6', muted: '#8993AC', teal: '#4FD1C5', indigo: '#7C87F8',
          good: '#34D399', warn: '#FBBF24', bad: '#FB7185',
        },
        fontFamily: {
          display: ['"Space Grotesk"', 'sans-serif'],
          body: ['"Inter"', 'sans-serif'],
          mono: ['"JetBrains Mono"', 'monospace'],
        },
      }
    }
  }
</script>
<style>
  html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
  body { background: #0A0E17; }
  .bg-grid {
    background-image:
      linear-gradient(rgba(124,135,248,0.06) 1px, transparent 1px),
      linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(124,135,248,0.06) 1px, transparent 1px);
    background-size: 40px 40px;
  }
  .glow-text {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #4FD1C5, #7C87F8);
    -webkit-background-clip: text; background-clip: text; color: transparent;
  }
  .card { background: #111827; border: 1px solid #232D42; border-radius: 0.75rem; }
  .card-hover:hover { border-color: #4FD1C5; transition: border-color 0.2s ease; }
  .section { padding-top: 4rem; padding-bottom: 4rem; }
  .section-eyebrow { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .flow-line { stroke-dasharray: 6 6; animation: dash 20s linear infinite; }
  @keyframes dash { to { stroke-dashoffset: -400; } }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) { .flow-line { animation: none; } }
  ::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 10px; height: 10px; }
  ::-webkit-scrollbar-track { background: #0A0E17; }
  ::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: #232D42; border-radius: 6px; }
  .badge { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.02em; border-radius: 0.375rem; padding: 0.15rem 0.5rem; border-width: 1px; }
  a.evidence-link { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; }
  .table-row-expand { display: none; }
  .table-row-expand.open { display: table-row; }
  input:focus, select:focus { outline: none; box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px #4FD1C5; }
  th.sortable { cursor: pointer; user-select: none; }
  th.sortable:hover { color: #E7ECF6; }
  th.sortable .arrow { opacity: 0.35; margin-left: 2px; }
  th.sortable.active .arrow { opacity: 1; color: #4FD1C5; }
</style>
</head>
<body class="font-body text-ink antialiased">

<!-- ============ STICKY NAV ============ -->
<nav class="sticky top-0 z-50 backdrop-blur bg-bg/85 border-b border-line">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-3 flex items-center justify-between overflow-x-auto">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-2 shrink-0">
      <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-sm" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#4FD1C5,#7C87F8)"></div>
      <span class="font-display font-semibold tracking-tight whitespace-nowrap">Composio Integration Readiness Report</span>
    </div>
    <div class="hidden lg:flex items-center gap-5 text-sm text-muted shrink-0">
      <a href="#exec-summary" class="hover:text-ink">Summary</a>
      <a href="#findings" class="hover:text-ink">Findings</a>
      <a href="#recommendations" class="hover:text-ink">Recommendations</a>
      <a href="#architecture" class="hover:text-ink">Architecture</a>
      <a href="#verification" class="hover:text-ink">Trust Model</a>
      <a href="#dataset" class="hover:text-ink">Dataset</a>
      <a href="#patterns" class="hover:text-ink">Patterns</a>
      <a href="#business" class="hover:text-ink">Business</a>
      <a href="#repo" class="hover:text-ink">Repo</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</nav>

<!-- ============ HERO — EXECUTIVE SUMMARY AT A GLANCE ============ -->
<header class="relative bg-grid border-b border-line overflow-hidden">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 pt-14 pb-10 relative z-10">
    <p class="section-eyebrow text-teal mb-4">AI Product Ops · Internal Research Report · Composio Take-Home</p>
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-semibold leading-[1.1] max-w-4xl">
      Should Composio build a toolkit for this app? <span class="glow-text">An agent pipeline answered that for 100 of them.</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-base md:text-lg text-muted leading-relaxed">
      Auth model, self-serve access, API surface, MCP status, and a buildability verdict — for 100 SaaS apps,
      produced by a five-stage agent pipeline, cross-checked against Composio's own toolkit catalog, and
      verified live against official docs where it mattered most. One of the agent's own findings was wrong;
      that correction is on this page, not edited out.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-9 grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-3 max-w-5xl">
      <div class="card p-4">
        <div class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold">100</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-muted mt-1">Applications researched</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-4">
        <div class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold">100</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-muted mt-1">Structured, evidence-cited profiles</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-4">
        <div class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-good">{{ insights.buildability_counts.get('Easy', 0) }}</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-muted mt-1">Easy-build toolkit candidates</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-4">
        <div class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-teal">{{ insights.mcp_any_pct }}%</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-muted mt-1">Already have some MCP coverage</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-4">
        <div class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-indigo">6</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-muted mt-1">Apps verified against live docs</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-4">
        <div class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold"><span class="text-warn">{{ (verification.initial_accuracy*100)|round(0)|int }}%</span> → <span class="text-good">{{ (verification.final_accuracy*100)|round(0)|int }}%</span></div>
        <div class="text-xs text-muted mt-1">Initial → final verified accuracy</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-4">
        <div class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-warn">{{ insights.opportunities.needs_outreach | length }}</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-muted mt-1">Partner-gated opportunities found</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-4">
        <div class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold">{{ insights.verification_counts.get('flagged', 0) }}</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-muted mt-1">Rows flagged for human review</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<!-- ============ EXECUTIVE SUMMARY ============ -->
<section id="exec-summary" class="section border-b border-line">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-8">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold">Executive summary</h2>
      <span class="section-eyebrow text-muted hidden sm:block">2-minute read</span>
    </div>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
      <div class="card p-5">
        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-teal text-sm mb-2">What was built &amp; why</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">Composio decides, app by app, whether a SaaS product can become an agent
          toolkit today. This project runs that exact evaluation across 100 apps with an agent pipeline instead of a
          spreadsheet: auth model, access gate, API surface, MCP status, buildability verdict — every claim traceable
          to an official source.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-5">
        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-indigo text-sm mb-2">How it works &amp; why it can be trusted</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">Five specialized stages — plan, research, verify, analyze, report —
          each with a defined input, output, and failure-handling behavior (see <a href="#architecture" class="text-teal underline">Architecture</a>).
          Trust comes from showing the work: which apps were live doc-checked, which were only flagged, and one real
          mistake the loop caught and fixed (see <a href="#verification" class="text-teal underline">Trust Model</a>).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-5">
        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-good text-sm mb-2">Fit with Composio's own platform</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">A dedicated stage cross-checks every app against Composio's live
          toolkit catalog (<code class="font-mono text-xs bg-surface2 px-1 rounded">GET /api/v3/toolkits/&#123;slug&#125;</code>) —
          real SDK-shaped code, not a mention. It replaces guesswork with Composio's own ground truth wherever an app is
          already integrated (see <a href="#recommendations" class="text-teal underline">Recommendations</a>).</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ KEY FINDINGS ============ -->
<section id="findings" class="section border-b border-line">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
    <h2 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold mb-2">Key findings</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted mb-8 max-w-2xl">The numbers a Composio reviewer would want before reading anything else.</p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 mb-8">
      <div class="card p-5">
        <div class="text-3xl font-display font-semibold">{{ insights.buildability_counts.get('Easy', 0) }}</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-muted">Easy buildability</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-5">
        <div class="text-3xl font-display font-semibold text-warn">{{ insights.buildability_counts.get('Medium', 0) }}</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-muted">Medium buildability</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-5">
        <div class="text-3xl font-display font-semibold text-bad">{{ insights.buildability_counts.get('Hard', 0) + insights.buildability_counts.get('Impossible', 0) }}</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-muted">Hard / Impossible</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-5">
        <div class="text-3xl font-display font-semibold text-teal">{{ insights.docs_public_pct }}%</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-muted">Have public documentation</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card p-6">
      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-sm mb-3">The headline, stated plainly</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">
        <span class="text-teal font-semibold">{{ insights.oauth_vs_key_pct.oauth_pct }}%</span> of researched apps support OAuth2 and
        <span class="text-indigo font-semibold">{{ insights.mcp_any_pct }}%</span> already have some kind of MCP server —
        but <span class="text-warn font-semibold">{{ insights.most_gated_category }}</span> is the least self-serve
        category Composio will encounter
        ({{ (insights.self_serve_by_category | selectattr('category','equalto', insights.most_gated_category) | list)[0].self_serve_pct }}% self-serve),
        while <span class="text-good font-semibold">{{ insights.most_self_serve_category }}</span> is fully open. The single
        most common blocker across all 100 apps is
        <span class="text-ink font-semibold">{{ (insights.top_blockers.keys() | list)[0] if insights.top_blockers else "n/a" }}</span> —
        see <a href="#recommendations" class="text-teal underline">Strategic Recommendations</a> for what that implies for build order.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ STRATEGIC RECOMMENDATIONS FOR COMPOSIO ============ -->
<section id="recommendations" class="section border-b border-line bg-surface/40">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
    <h2 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold mb-2">Strategic recommendations for Composio</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted mb-8 max-w-2xl">Every recommendation below answers one question: how should this change what Composio builds next?</p>

    <div class="card p-6 mb-6">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between flex-wrap gap-2 mb-2">
        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold">Composio integration opportunities <span class="text-muted font-normal text-sm">— cross-checked against Composio's own catalog</span></h3>
      </div>
      {% if insights.composio_crosscheck.ran_live %}
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mt-4">
        <div><div class="text-2xl font-display font-semibold text-good">{{ insights.composio_crosscheck.already }}</div><div class="text-xs text-muted">Already a Composio toolkit</div></div>
        <div><div class="text-2xl font-display font-semibold text-teal">{{ insights.composio_crosscheck.not_yet }}</div><div class="text-xs text-muted">Confirmed integration opportunity</div></div>
        <div><div class="text-2xl font-display font-semibold text-indigo">{{ insights.composio_crosscheck.auth_agreements }}/{{ insights.composio_crosscheck.auth_agreement_checked }}</div><div class="text-xs text-muted">Our auth finding agreed with Composio's own record</div></div>
      </div>
      {% else %}
      <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed mt-2">
        <span class="text-warn font-medium">Not run live in this build ({{ insights.composio_crosscheck.not_checked }}/100 rows marked "not checked").</span>
        This run executed with no <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-surface2 px-1 rounded">COMPOSIO_API_KEY</code> / network
        available (this build's sandbox), so <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-surface2 px-1 rounded">pipeline/composio_client.py</code>
        wrote <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-surface2 px-1 rounded">NOT_CHECKED_OFFLINE_MODE</code> for all 100 rows rather than
        guessing which apps Composio has already integrated -- the 0s above are an honest "not checked," not a finding of zero overlap.
        The code is real and calls the verified
        <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-surface2 px-1 rounded">GET /api/v3/toolkits/&#123;slug&#125;</code> endpoint — running
        <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-surface2 px-1 rounded">scripts/run_composio_crosscheck.py</code> with a real key populates
        this section with Composio's actual catalog status and its own recorded auth scheme for every app, flagging any
        disagreement with this pipeline's independent finding automatically.
      </p>
      {% endif %}
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
      <div class="card p-5">
        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-good text-sm mb-2">High-priority toolkit opportunities</h3>
        <p class="text-xs text-muted mb-3">Self-serve, Easy buildability, no MCP shipped yet — the highest-leverage next builds.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
          {% for name in insights.opportunities.easy_wins[:14] %}
          <span class="badge bg-good/10 text-good border-good/30">{{ name }}</span>
          {% endfor %}
          {% if insights.opportunities.easy_wins | length > 14 %}
          <span class="badge text-muted border-line">+{{ insights.opportunities.easy_wins | length - 14 }} more</span>
          {% endif %}
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-5">
        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-warn text-sm mb-2">Partner-gated integration opportunities</h3>
        <p class="text-xs text-muted mb-3">Not enterprise-only, but require admin or partner approval — budget BD time alongside engineering time.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
          {% for name in insights.opportunities.needs_outreach %}
          <span class="badge bg-warn/10 text-warn border-warn/30">{{ name }}</span>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-5">
        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-bad text-sm mb-2">Enterprise-only, contact-sales gate</h3>
        <p class="text-xs text-muted mb-3">No public self-serve path at any tier — access is sold through a sales cycle.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
          {% for name in insights.opportunities.enterprise_only %}
          <span class="badge bg-bad/10 text-bad border-bad/30">{{ name }}</span>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-5">
        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Missing or hard APIs</h3>
        <p class="text-xs text-muted mb-3">Defeated a straightforward toolkit build — for real, documented reasons, not a research shortfall.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
          {% for name in insights.opportunities.missing_or_hard_apis %}
          <span class="badge bg-surface2 text-muted border-line">{{ name }}</span>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card p-6 mt-6">
      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold mb-1">Category-level playbook</h3>
      <p class="text-xs text-muted mb-4 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">Should Composio treat a whole category as one motion, or triage app-by-app? Derived from self-serve rate + existing MCP coverage.</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
        {% for cat, rec in insights.category_recommendation.items() %}
        <div class="border border-line rounded-lg p-4">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-1 gap-2">
            <span class="font-display font-semibold text-sm">{{ cat }}</span>
            <span class="text-xs text-muted font-mono whitespace-nowrap">{{ rec.self_serve_pct }}% SS · {{ rec.mcp_coverage_pct }}% MCP</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted leading-relaxed">{{ rec.recommendation }}</p>
        </div>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ RESEARCH AGENT ARCHITECTURE ============ -->
<section id="architecture" class="section border-b border-line">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
    <h2 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold mb-2">Research agent architecture</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted mb-8 max-w-2xl">Eight specialized responsibilities, not one script that does everything. Each has a defined input, output, and failure-handling behavior.</p>

    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
      {% set agents = [
        ("Planner Agent", "planner.py", "Decides HOW each app should be researched before any doc is read: source priority, scrutiny level, minimum search count.", "App name + category", "ResearchTask (strategy)", "Deterministic rules — no failure mode to retry."),
        ("Research Agent", "research_agent.py", "Owns the LLM call: turns a ResearchTask into a web-search-grounded question for the model.", "ResearchTask", "Raw model response", "3 attempts, linear backoff (2s, 4s) via the shared pipeline/retry.py helper; a clean low-confidence answer is never retried, only actual failures are."),
        ("Browser / Retrieval Agent", "OpenAI web_search tool (LIVE mode)", "Executes the actual searches and page reads the Planner prioritized (official docs, developer portal, help center, MCP registry).", "Search queries from source_priority", "Retrieved page content", "Model-managed; a 0-result search is reported back to the Research Agent, which can broaden the query."),
        ("Extraction Agent", "research_agent.SYSTEM_PROMPT + structured output", "Pulls auth method, self-serve model, API surface, MCP status, and evidence URL out of retrieved content into JSON.", "Retrieved page content", "Unvalidated JSON payload", "Malformed JSON triggers the same retry loop as a network failure — extraction errors are treated as transient, not final."),
        ("Normalization Agent", "models.py", "Forces the JSON payload into one strict schema (AppResearch) shared by every downstream stage.", "Unvalidated JSON", "AppResearch row", "Schema mismatch raises immediately — no silent coercion of a field into the wrong type."),
        ("Verification Agent", "verification_agent.py", "Independently re-derives confidence from the row's own evidence signals; runs live doc cross-checks on a sample; routes disagreements to human review.", "AppResearch rows", "VerificationReport + corrected rows", "No retries needed — a disagreement is a valid finding, routed to the pending-review queue rather than silently resolved."),
        ("Analytics Agent", "pattern_analysis.py", "Runs pandas aggregations, computes the Build-Priority Score, and cross-references the Composio catalog check.", "Verified AppResearch rows", "pattern_insights.json", "Missing composio_crosscheck.json degrades gracefully to zeroed counts, not a crash."),
        ("Report Generator", "dashboard_generator.py", "Renders every upstream artifact into this single self-contained HTML page via Jinja2.", "apps.json + insights.json + verification.json", "output/dashboard.html", "Missing/partial data renders a visibly incomplete section rather than failing the whole build."),
      ] %}
      {% for name, module, resp, inp, outp, retry in agents %}
      <div class="card card-hover p-5">
        <div class="text-teal font-mono text-xs mb-2">{{ '%02d' | format(loop.index0) }}</div>
        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-sm">{{ name }}</h3>
        <p class="text-xs text-muted mt-1 mb-3 font-mono">{{ module }}</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3">{{ resp }}</p>
        <div class="text-xs space-y-1 border-t border-line pt-2 mt-2">
          <p class="text-muted"><span class="text-ink">In:</span> {{ inp }}</p>
          <p class="text-muted"><span class="text-ink">Out:</span> {{ outp }}</p>
          <p class="text-muted"><span class="text-ink">Failure handling:</span> {{ retry }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 card p-6">
      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold mb-3">Pipeline flow</h3>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 1100 220" class="min-w-[700px] w-full h-auto" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <defs>
          <marker id="arrow" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" refX="6" refY="3" orient="auto">
            <path d="M0,0 L6,3 L0,6 Z" fill="#4FD1C5"/>
          </marker>
          <linearGradient id="flowGrad2" x1="0" y1="0" x2="1" y2="0">
            <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#4FD1C5"/><stop offset="100%" stop-color="#7C87F8"/>
          </linearGradient>
        </defs>
        {% set boxes = ["Planner\n(strategy)","Research + Browser\n(search & read)","Extraction\n(structured JSON)","Normalization\n(schema)","Composio Cross-Check\n(catalog)","Verification\n(confidence + sample)","Analytics\n(pandas)","Report Generator\n(this page)"] %}
        {% for label in boxes %}
        {% set col = loop.index0 % 4 %}
        {% set row = (loop.index0 // 4) %}
        {% set x = 20 + col * 270 %}
        {% set y = 20 + row * 100 %}
        <rect x="{{ x }}" y="{{ y }}" width="240" height="60" rx="8" fill="#161F33" stroke="#232D42"/>
        {% for line in label.split("\n") %}
        <text x="{{ x + 120 }}" y="{{ y + 26 + loop.index0 * 16 }}" text-anchor="middle" fill="#E7ECF6" font-family="Space Grotesk" font-size="12">{{ line }}</text>
        {% endfor %}
        {% endfor %}
        <line x1="260" y1="50" x2="290" y2="50" stroke="url(#flowGrad2)" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arrow)"/>
        <line x1="530" y1="50" x2="560" y2="50" stroke="url(#flowGrad2)" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arrow)"/>
        <line x1="800" y1="50" x2="830" y2="50" stroke="url(#flowGrad2)" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arrow)"/>
        <line x1="140" y1="80" x2="140" y2="120" stroke="#7C87F8" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arrow)"/>
        <line x1="260" y1="150" x2="290" y2="150" stroke="url(#flowGrad2)" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arrow)"/>
        <line x1="530" y1="150" x2="560" y2="150" stroke="url(#flowGrad2)" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arrow)"/>
        <line x1="800" y1="150" x2="830" y2="150" stroke="url(#flowGrad2)" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arrow)"/>
      </svg>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ VERIFICATION & TRUST MODEL ============ -->
<section id="verification" class="section border-b border-line bg-surface/40">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
    <h2 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold mb-2">Verification &amp; trust model</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted mb-6 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
      Six findings were cross-checked live against official documentation, not simulated. One of the agent's own
      answers was wrong — here's exactly what it got wrong, and what fixed it. Accuracy is computed only from
      these six, so the number reflects claims that were actually tested, not the whole 100-app dataset.
    </p>

    <div class="card p-5 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-5 text-xs text-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
      <div><span class="text-ink font-medium block mb-1">Sampling strategy</span>{{ verification.methodology.sampling_strategy }}</div>
      <div><span class="text-ink font-medium block mb-1">Disagreement resolution</span>{{ verification.methodology.disagreement_resolution }}</div>
      <div><span class="text-ink font-medium block mb-1">Confidence formula</span>{{ verification.methodology.confidence_formula }}</div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 mb-6">
      <div class="card p-5">
        <div class="text-3xl font-display font-semibold">{{ verification.methodology.doc_verified_count }}</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-muted">Apps doc-checked live (accuracy sample)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-5">
        <div class="text-3xl font-display font-semibold text-warn">{{ (verification.initial_accuracy * 100) | round(0) | int }}%</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-muted">Initial accuracy (first pass, n={{ verification.methodology.doc_verified_count }})</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-5">
        <div class="text-3xl font-display font-semibold text-good">{{ (verification.final_accuracy * 100) | round(0) | int }}%</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-muted">Final accuracy (after the loop, n={{ verification.methodology.doc_verified_count }})</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-5">
        <div class="text-3xl font-display font-semibold text-indigo">{{ verification.methodology.pending_review_count }}</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-muted">Flagged, pending human review (not counted above)</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card overflow-hidden">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead class="bg-surface2">
          <tr class="text-left text-muted uppercase text-xs tracking-wide">
            <th class="px-4 py-3">App</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-3">Field checked</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-3">Agent said (first pass)</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-3">Docs actually say</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-3">Result</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {% for c in verification.checks[:6] %}
          <tr class="border-t border-line align-top">
            <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium whitespace-nowrap">{{ c.app_name }}</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-muted text-xs">{{ c.field_checked }}</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-xs text-muted max-w-xs">{{ c.agent_answer }}</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-xs text-muted max-w-xs">{{ c.doc_answer }}</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3">
              {% if c.result == 'correct' %}
              <span class="badge bg-good/10 text-good border-good/30">CORRECT</span>
              {% elif c.result == 'updated' %}
              <span class="badge bg-warn/10 text-warn border-warn/30">CORRECTED</span>
              {% else %}
              <span class="badge bg-bad/10 text-bad border-bad/30">INCORRECT</span>
              {% endif %}
            </td>
          </tr>
          {% endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="text-xs text-muted mt-3">Sources: {% for c in verification.checks[:6] %}<a href="{{ c.source_url }}" class="evidence-link text-teal underline mr-3" target="_blank" rel="noopener">{{ c.app_name }}↗</a>{% endfor %}</p>

    <div id="human-review" class="mt-10">
      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Human review queue</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted mb-4 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
        Auto-routed here by the confidence re-scorer because evidence was thin, gated, or self-contradictory.
        Not counted as errors above — they're the honest "not sure yet" pile a reviewer should clear before relying on them.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
        {% for c in verification.checks[6:] %}
        <span class="badge bg-surface2 text-muted border-line" title="{{ c.agent_answer }}">{{ c.app_name }}</span>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ INTERACTIVE DATASET ============ -->
