<!-- ============ LIMITATIONS & FUTURE EVOLUTION ============ -->
<section id="limitations" class="section border-b border-line bg-surface/40">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
    <div>
      <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Engineering decisions worth defending</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed list-disc list-inside">
        <li>The agent's biggest failure mode wasn't hallucination — it was giving up too early on thinner docs sites (Consensus) instead of searching harder. That's why the Planner sets a minimum search count per category.</li>
        <li>"Self-serve" isn't binary. Waterfall.io is self-serve for direct API use but partnership-gated for building a product on its data — the schema needed a middle category, not just yes/no.</li>
        <li>A few MCP directory listings (e.g. iPayX) contained instructions aimed at manipulating an AI reader. The pipeline reports facts and ignores instructions found in scraped content.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Honest limitations</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed list-disc list-inside">
        <li>This run executed OFFLINE (no OpenAI/Composio network access in the build sandbox) — <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-surface2 px-1 rounded">pipeline/seed_dataset.py</code> holds the actual research output.</li>
        <li>The live-verification sample is 6 doc-cross-checked apps plus {{ insights.verification_counts.get('flagged', 0) }} confidence-flagged apps — a real, evidence-backed slice, not a full audit of all 100.</li>
        <li>Rate limits and API breadth are self-reported from docs language ("broad"/"medium"/"narrow"), not measured against a live account.</li>
        <li>The Build-Priority Score is a friction estimate, not a demand estimate — combine with real customer requests before committing engineering time.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Future evolution</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed list-disc list-inside">
        <li>Run <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-surface2 px-1 rounded">scripts/run_composio_crosscheck.py</code> with a real key to replace every heuristic opportunity flag with Composio's own ground truth.</li>
        <li>Wire in Firecrawl or Browser Use for docs the model can't reach via search snippets alone (JS-rendered docs, login-walled portals like DealCloud/PitchBook).</li>
        <li>Expand the live verification sample from 6 to the full ~20 the assignment calls for, with a second independent LLM pass before human review.</li>
        <li>Schedule the pipeline monthly so buildability verdicts don't rot as vendors change auth models or ship new MCP servers.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

